74void EphemeronHashTable::set_key(int index, Tagged<Object> value) {
75 DCHECK_NE(GetReadOnlyRoots().fixed_cow_array_map(), map());
76 DCHECK(IsEphemeronHashTable(*this));
77 DCHECK_GE(index, 0);
78 DCHECK_LT(index, this->length());
79 int offset = kHeaderSize + index * kTaggedSize;
80 RELAXED_WRITE_FIELD(*this, offset, value);
81 EPHEMERON_KEY_WRITE_BARRIER(*this, offset, value);
82}
83
84void EphemeronHashTable::set_key(int index, Tagged<Object> value,
85 WriteBarrierMode mode) {
86 DCHECK_NE(GetReadOnlyRoots().fixed_cow_array_map(), map());
87 DCHECK(IsEphemeronHashTable(*this));
88 DCHECK_GE(index, 0);
89 DCHECK_LT(index, this->length());
90 int offset = kHeaderSize + index * kTaggedSize;
91 RELAXED_WRITE_FIELD(*this, offset, value);
92 CONDITIONAL_EPHEMERON_KEY_WRITE_BARRIER(*this, offset, value, mode);
93}

121 SetNumberOfElements(NumberOfElements() - n);
122 SetNumberOfDeletedElements(NumberOfDeletedElements() + n);

125// static
126int HashTableBase::ComputeCapacity(int at_least_space_for) {
127 // Add 50% slack to make slot collisions sufficiently unlikely.
128 // See matching computation in HashTable::HasSufficientCapacityToAdd().
129 // Must be kept in sync with CodeStubAssembler::HashTableComputeCapacity().
130 int raw_cap = at_least_space_for + (at_least_space_for >> 1);
131 int capacity = base::bits::RoundUpToPowerOfTwo32(raw_cap);
132 return std::max({capacity, kMinCapacity});
133}

169template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
170template <typename IsolateT>
171InternalIndex HashTable<Derived, Shape>::FindEntry(IsolateT* isolate, Key key) {
172 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
173 return FindEntry(isolate, roots, key, TodoShape::Hash(roots, key));
174}
175
176// Find entry for key otherwise return kNotFound.
177template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
178InternalIndex HashTable<Derived, Shape>::FindEntry(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
179 ReadOnlyRoots roots, Key key,
180 int32_t hash) {
181 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
182 uint32_t capacity = Capacity();
183 uint32_t count = 1;
184 Tagged<Object> undefined = roots.undefined_value();
185 Tagged<Object> the_hole = roots.the_hole_value();
186 DCHECK_EQ(TodoShape::Hash(roots, key), static_cast<uint32_t>(hash));
187 // EnsureCapacity will guarantee the hash table is never full.
188 for (InternalIndex entry = FirstProbe(hash, capacity);;
189 entry = NextProbe(entry, count++, capacity)) {
190 Tagged<Object> element = KeyAt(cage_base, entry);
191 // Empty entry. Uses raw unchecked accessors because it is called by the
192 // string table during bootstrapping.
193 if (element == undefined) return InternalIndex::NotFound();
194 if (TodoShape::kMatchNeedsHoleCheck && element == the_hole) continue;
195 if (TodoShape::IsMatch(key, element)) return entry;
196 }
197}

199template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
200template <typename IsolateT>
201InternalIndex HashTable<Derived, Shape>::FindInsertionEntry(IsolateT* isolate,
202 uint32_t hash) {
203 return FindInsertionEntry(isolate, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate), hash);
204}

206// static
207template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
208bool HashTable<Derived, Shape>::IsKey(ReadOnlyRoots roots, Tagged<Object> k) {
209 // TODO(leszeks): Dictionaries that don't delete could skip the hole check.
210 return k != roots.unchecked_undefined_value() &&
211 k != roots.unchecked_the_hole_value();
212}
213
214template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
215bool HashTable<Derived, Shape>::ToKey(ReadOnlyRoots roots, InternalIndex entry,
216 Tagged<Object>* out_k) {
217 Tagged<Object> k = KeyAt(entry);
218 if (!IsKey(roots, k)) return false;
219 *out_k = TodoShape::Unwrap(k);
220 return true;
221}
222
223template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
224bool HashTable<Derived, Shape>::ToKey(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
225 InternalIndex entry,
226 Tagged<Object>* out_k) {
227 Tagged<Object> k = KeyAt(cage_base, entry);
228 if (!IsKey(GetReadOnlyRoots(cage_base), k)) return false;
229 *out_k = TodoShape::Unwrap(k);
230 return true;
231}

233template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
234Tagged<Object> HashTable<Derived, Shape>::KeyAt(InternalIndex entry) {
235 PtrComprCageBase cage_base = GetPtrComprCageBase(*this);
236 return KeyAt(cage_base, entry);
237}

279template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
280void HashTable<Derived, Shape>::SetCapacity(int capacity) {
281 // To scale a computed hash code to fit within the hash table, we
282 // use bit-wise AND with a mask, so the capacity must be positive
283 // and non-zero.
284 DCHECK_GT(capacity, 0);
285 DCHECK_LE(capacity, kMaxCapacity);
286 set(kCapacityIndex, Smi::FromInt(capacity));
287}

289bool ObjectHashSet::Has(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> key, int32_t hash) {
290 return FindEntry(isolate, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate), key, hash).is_found();
291}
292
293bool ObjectHashSet::Has(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Object> key) {
294 Tagged<Object> hash = Object::GetHash(*key);
295 if (!IsSmi(hash)) return false;
296 return FindEntry(isolate, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate), key, Smi::ToInt(hash))
297 .is_found();
298}

342template <typename IsolateT>
343Handle<NameToIndexHashTable> NameToIndexHashTable::Add(
344 IsolateT* isolate, Handle<NameToIndexHashTable> table, Handle<Name> key,
345 int32_t index) {
346 DCHECK_GE(index, 0);
347 // Validate that the key is absent.
348 SLOW_DCHECK(table->FindEntry(isolate, key).is_not_found());
349 // Check whether the dictionary should be extended.
350 table = EnsureCapacity(isolate, table);
351 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
352 Tagged<NameToIndexHashTable> raw_table = *table;
353 // Compute the key object.
354 InternalIndex entry = raw_table->FindInsertionEntry(isolate, key->hash());
355 raw_table->set(EntryToIndex(entry), *key);
356 raw_table->set(EntryToValueIndex(entry), Smi::FromInt(index));
357 raw_table->ElementAdded();
358 return table;
359}
